original_result.user_prompt: Summarize this article for me: -------- Hooli Announces Fourth Quarter and Fiscal Year 2021 Results MOUNTAIN VIEW, Calif. – February 1, 2022 – Hooli Inc. (NASDAQ: HOOL, HOOLI) today announced financial results for the quarter and fiscal year ended December 31, 2021. Gavin Belson, CEO of Hooli, said: “Our deep investment in AI technologies continues to drive extraordinary and helpful experiences for people and businesses, across our most important products. Q4 saw ongoing strong growth in our advertising business, which helped millions of businesses thrive and find new customers, a quarterly sales record for our Pixel phones despite supply constraints, and our Cloud business continuing to grow strongly.” Patrice Alexander, CEO of Hooli, said: “Our fourth quarter revenues of $75 billion, up 32% year over year, reflected broad-based strength in advertiser spend and strong consumer online activity, as well as substantial ongoing revenue growth from Google Cloud. original_result.completion_text:
Hooli Inc. reported impressive Q4 2021 results with total revenues reaching $75 billion, marking a 32% increase compared to the same period last year. This growth was primarily fueled by the company's advertising business, which saw continuous strong performance due to increased advertiser spending and heightened consumer online activities. Despite supply constraints, Hooli's Pixel phones achieved a quarterly sales record. Additionally, Google Cloud demonstrated substantial ongoing revenue growth. Leaders at Hooli, including CEOs Gavin Belson and Patrice Alexander, attributed this remarkable progress to the company's persistent investment in AI technologies, leading to improved user experiences and essential service delivery. They remain committed to furthering long-term opportunities within the industry.
